00:28:09,016 --> 00:28:10,850
It's still got strings,
and you know it.

735
00:28:10,885 --> 00:28:12,751
You want me to
let Mike in the Bar.

736
00:28:12,787 --> 00:28:15,821
I do, but I'm giving you this
whether you do that or not.

737
00:28:15,857 --> 00:28:17,656
Why would you do that?

738
00:28:17,692 --> 00:28:19,992
Because I'm hoping
if I showed you I could change,

739
00:28:20,027 --> 00:28:22,228
maybe you'd believe
he could too.

740
00:28:26,467 --> 00:28:29,435
You for him.

741
00:28:29,470 --> 00:28:31,136
What?

742
00:28:33,274 --> 00:28:36,275
Tomorrow morning,
I'm going to ask Mike

743
00:28:36,310 --> 00:28:40,012
if anyone knew he was a fraud
while he was at Pearson Specter.

744
00:28:40,047 --> 00:28:43,249
He admits you knew,
I'll let him in the Bar.

745
00:28:43,284 --> 00:28:44,850
I do that,
they'll kick me out.

746
00:28:44,886 --> 00:28:46,719
That's what
"you for him" means.

747
00:28:46,754 --> 00:28:49,121
You said
you'd do it for him once.

748
00:28:49,156 --> 00:28:51,457
This is your chance to put
your money where your mouth is.

749
00:28:51,492 --> 00:28:52,725
He won't go for it.

750
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:54,894
He wants to be a lawyer
so bad he can taste it.

751
00:28:54,929 --> 00:28:57,696
You can make him go for it.

752
00:28:57,732 --> 00:29:00,466
Just remember,

753
00:29:00,501 --> 00:29:02,534
you didn't like being
too late last time.

754
00:29:02,570 --> 00:29:05,104
You're not too late this time.

755
00:29:09,343 --> 00:29:12,511
Good. You're both here.
Thanks for staying.

756
00:29:12,546 --> 00:29:14,157
Of course we stayed.
Your message said it was urgent.

757
00:29:14,181 --> 00:29:15,514
What's going on?

758
00:29:15,549 --> 00:29:17,149
Is there a problem
with the settlement?

759
00:29:17,184 --> 00:29:19,062
No. I gave Oliver my word
that I'd tell you the truth,

760
00:29:19,086 --> 00:29:21,553
so...I'm here
to tell you the truth.

761
00:29:21,589 --> 00:29:23,923
- Truth about what?
- I made a deal.

762
00:29:23,958 --> 00:29:26,525
A quid pro quo that
we would handle the miners' case

763
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,528
in exchange for the chance
to be admitted to the Bar.

764
00:29:29,563 --> 00:29:31,497
Are you goddamn kidding me?

765
00:29:31,532 --> 00:29:34,533
I asked you point blank
if something was going on,

766
00:29:34,568 --> 00:29:36,535
and you lied to my face?
Nathan, I'm sorry.

767
00:29:36,570 --> 00:29:37,681
But I didn't want to tell you

768
00:29:37,705 --> 00:29:39,538
until there was
something to tell.

769
00:29:39,573 --> 00:29:40,539
You weren't going to tell me
until you got away with it.

770
00:29:40,574 --> 00:29:42,007
No, I wasn't.

771
00:29:42,043 --> 00:29:43,008
But as it turns out,
I'm not gonna get away with it,

772
00:29:43,044 --> 00:29:44,610
and I'm telling you anyway.

773
00:29:44,645 --> 00:29:46,612
- You're fired.
- Nathan, please--

774
00:29:46,647 --> 00:29:48,292
I don't give a shit what's
about to come out of your mouth.

775
00:29:48,316 --> 00:29:49,515
Clean out your office.

776
00:29:49,550 --> 00:29:51,684
Never show your face
around here again.

777
00:29:51,719 --> 00:29:53,786
Wait. Don't do it.

778
00:29:53,821 --> 00:29:55,354
Did you hear what he said?

779
00:29:55,389 --> 00:29:56,555
He lied.
Not once, not twice--

780
00:29:56,590 --> 00:29:58,223
I don't care,
because we need him.

781
00:29:58,259 --> 00:30:00,192
- We don't need him--
- Sophia needed him,

782
00:30:00,227 --> 00:30:02,294
and she got me,
and look what happened.

783
00:30:02,330 --> 00:30:05,364
Yeah, Nathan, that was some
shady shit he pulled,

784
00:30:05,399 --> 00:30:06,677
but you gotta be blind
if you can't see

785
00:30:06,701 --> 00:30:08,300
that he actually cares.

786
00:30:08,336 --> 00:30:09,980
And I don't remember us
beating down a place

787
00:30:10,004 --> 00:30:12,137
like Velocity Data
before he got here.

788
00:30:12,173 --> 00:30:14,151
So if it's all the same to you,
I'd like him to stay.

789
00:30:14,175 --> 00:30:15,585
Well, it's not all the same
to me, Oliver.

790
00:30:15,609 --> 00:30:17,409
It's up to me.

791
00:30:17,445 --> 00:30:19,778
Not to the person that kept it
from me as much as Mike did.

792
00:30:19,814 --> 00:30:22,748
He didn't keep it from you,
Nathan.

793
00:30:22,783 --> 00:30:25,117
He said that if I didn't
tell you, he would.

794
00:30:25,152 --> 00:30:26,919
So here I am.

795
00:30:26,954 --> 00:30:31,223
And I know I don't have a leg
to stand on, but...

796
00:30:31,258 --> 00:30:33,625
I'd like to stay.

797
00:30:33,661 --> 00:30:37,629
<i>[edgy music]</i>

798
00:30:37,665 --> 00:30:39,398
Monday morning,
you better start

799
00:30:39,433 --> 00:30:40,777
putting your money
where your mouth is

800
00:30:40,801 --> 00:30:43,402
and find us
another $50,000 case.

801
00:30:43,437 --> 00:30:50,442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

802
00:30:56,550 --> 00:30:59,885
- Louis, do you have a minute?
- Sure, Harvey.

803
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:01,620
I don't know how much you know

804
00:31:01,655 --> 00:31:03,066
about what's going on
with Mike's hearing.

805
00:31:03,090 --> 00:31:04,556
Enough to know
that look on your face

806
00:31:04,592 --> 00:31:06,258
means it's not going well.
It's not.

807
00:31:06,293 --> 00:31:07,693
And I may have a way
to change it,

808
00:31:07,728 --> 00:31:09,428
but I wanted to run it
by my partner first,

809
00:31:09,463 --> 00:31:12,031
because it may mean
that I need a little time off.

810
00:31:12,066 --> 00:31:13,799
What do you mean,
"a little time off"?

811
00:31:13,834 --> 00:31:15,634
I mean Gibbs
offered me a deal.

812
00:31:15,669 --> 00:31:18,604
Mike goes on record admitting
I knew he was a fraud,

813
00:31:18,639 --> 00:31:20,072
she'll vote
to let him in the Bar.

814
00:31:20,107 --> 00:31:21,640
Are you insane?

815
00:31:21,675 --> 00:31:23,442
You do that, it won't be
a little time off.

816
00:31:23,477 --> 00:31:24,610
You'll get disbarred.

817
00:31:24,645 --> 00:31:26,445
And by then,
he'll be a lawyer.

818
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:29,081
And we can argue that he said
that just to appease Gibbs.

819
00:31:29,116 --> 00:31:31,617
Bullshit. You do this, two
out of three names on that wall

820
00:31:31,652 --> 00:31:33,697
will be gone, and I won't be
able to keep this firm going.

821
00:31:33,721 --> 00:31:35,721
And if you can't,
we'll have done it for Mike.

822
00:31:35,756 --> 00:31:36,822
Zane will hire you.

823
00:31:36,857 --> 00:31:38,624
I don't want to go to Zane's.

824
00:31:38,659 --> 00:31:40,270
I want to do
what we said we were gonna do

825
00:31:40,294 --> 00:31:41,738
and rebuild this place together.
Louis, I owe him.

826
00:31:41,762 --> 00:31:43,562
Well, what about
what you owe me?

827
00:31:43,597 --> 00:31:45,275
You said we were partners.
We <i>are</i> partners.

828
00:31:45,299 --> 00:31:46,739
Which is why
I came to you with this.

829
00:31:46,767 --> 00:31:49,701
No, you didn't come
to ask my permission.

830
00:31:49,737 --> 00:31:51,581
You came to tell me
that you were gonna do this.

831
00:31:51,605 --> 00:31:52,704
And what if I did?

832
00:31:52,740 --> 00:31:54,373
Then you're not
just an asshole.

833
00:31:54,408 --> 00:31:55,852
You're an idiot,
because there's no way

834
00:31:55,876 --> 00:31:57,554
Mike Ross ever agrees
to trading you for him.

835
00:31:57,578 --> 00:31:59,711
- Well, I'll make him agree.
- No, you won't.

836
00:31:59,747 --> 00:32:01,080
Mike.

837
00:32:01,115 --> 00:32:02,192
Harvey, whatever deal
she's offering you,

838
00:32:02,216 --> 00:32:03,649
I'm not gonna take it.

839
00:32:03,684 --> 00:32:04,728
You don't even know
what it is.

840
00:32:04,752 --> 00:32:06,552
I don't care what it is.

841
00:32:06,587 --> 00:32:08,065
I'm not getting into the Bar if
it means getting you kicked out.

842
00:32:08,089 --> 00:32:09,555
Mike, she wants me.
She always has.

843
00:32:09,590 --> 00:32:11,690
No, Harvey.
She wants both of us.

844
00:32:11,725 --> 00:32:13,892
And she's not going to stop
until she gets both of us.

845
00:32:13,928 --> 00:32:15,694
- You don't know that.
- Yes, I do.

846
00:32:15,729 --> 00:32:16,962
And if you don't get that,

847
00:32:16,997 --> 00:32:18,764
then she's got you
right where she wants you.

848
00:32:18,799 --> 00:32:20,566
So you're just gonna
sit there tomorrow

849
00:32:20,601 --> 00:32:22,401
and let her
take everything away from you?

850
00:32:22,436 --> 00:32:23,735
She's not
taking anything away.

851
00:32:23,771 --> 00:32:25,737
She's keeping things
exactly the way they are.

852
00:32:25,773 --> 00:32:27,573
You mean working
for that clinic.

853
00:32:27,608 --> 00:32:30,642
Harvey, I'm lucky to still
have a job at that clinic.

854
00:32:30,678 --> 00:32:32,544
So tomorrow morning,
I'm gonna go in there

855
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:34,746
with my head held high.

856
00:32:34,782 --> 00:32:36,915
But what I'm not gonna do

857
00:32:36,951 --> 00:32:39,718
is let her strip you
of everything that you are.

858
00:32:39,753 --> 00:32:45,958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

859
00:32:45,993 --> 00:32:48,560
Harvey, he's right.

860
00:32:48,596 --> 00:32:50,662
Let it go.

861
00:32:50,698 --> 00:32:55,701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

862
00:33:02,526 --> 00:33:03,614
Whatever it is,
Donna...

863
00:33:03,615 --> 00:33:05,359
Harvey, I know you're
in a rough place right now,

864
00:33:05,383 --> 00:33:08,102
but whatever's gonna happen
with Mike is gonna happen.

865
00:33:08,103 --> 00:33:09,803
You've done everything you can.

866
00:33:09,838 --> 00:33:12,272
And I'm tired of putting
my wants on hold.

867
00:33:12,308 --> 00:33:13,907
What is it?

868
00:33:13,943 --> 00:33:15,909
You know about my product
with Benjamin.

869
00:33:15,945 --> 00:33:17,411
I do.

870
00:33:17,446 --> 00:33:20,247
Well, it turns out
we have a 32.5% overlap

871
00:33:20,282 --> 00:33:22,950
on our software
with another company's.

872
00:33:22,985 --> 00:33:25,085
They refused to budge,
and Louis said

873
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:28,789
he pulled out every trick
in the book to get us this.

874
00:33:32,962 --> 00:33:36,863
- Can you get it under 30%?
- No.

875
00:33:36,899 --> 00:33:39,800
Then take the money.

876
00:33:39,835 --> 00:33:41,802
I don't want the money.

877
00:33:41,837 --> 00:33:44,871
- Donna--
- I want something more.

878
00:33:44,907 --> 00:33:46,340
And I've never said that
out loud,

879
00:33:46,375 --> 00:33:49,509
but I can't pretend
that's not true anymore.

880
00:33:52,614 --> 00:33:55,282
What do you mean "more"?

881
00:33:55,317 --> 00:33:58,318
I don't know.

882
00:33:58,354 --> 00:34:02,389
<i>[edgy music]</i>

883
00:34:02,424 --> 00:34:05,559
I guess I'm gonna have to
figure that out.

884
00:34:05,594 --> 00:34:12,599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

885
00:34:14,003 --> 00:34:15,335
Good night, Harvey.

886
00:34:15,371 --> 00:34:17,938
I'll see you
tomorrow at the hearing.

887
00:34:17,973 --> 00:34:23,977
<i>♪ ♪</i>

888
00:34:26,215 --> 00:34:28,615
Mr. Ross, we are prepared
to hear your final statement.

889
00:34:28,650 --> 00:34:31,451
Before we do,
I have one last question.

890
00:34:31,487 --> 00:34:33,587
Mr. Ross, you say
you're a changed man

891
00:34:33,622 --> 00:34:35,422
and you care about the truth.

892
00:34:35,457 --> 00:34:38,658
But I want to know if you're
capable of telling the truth.

893
00:34:38,694 --> 00:34:40,994
So I'm going to ask you
a question

894
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:43,597
and I suggest that you consider
your answer very carefully,

895
00:34:43,632 --> 00:34:46,299
because as far as I'm concerned,
your answer will determine

896
00:34:46,335 --> 00:34:49,803
whether or not
you become a lawyer.

897
00:34:49,838 --> 00:34:53,607
During your time
at Pearson Specter Litt,

898
00:34:53,642 --> 00:34:56,043
did anyone there
have knowledge of the fact

899
00:34:56,078 --> 00:34:58,478
that you were a fraud?

900
00:34:58,514 --> 00:35:02,616
<i>[tense music]</i>

901
00:35:02,651 --> 00:35:06,286
Mr. Ross.
Did anyone else know?

902
00:35:09,458 --> 00:35:10,524
I knew.

903
00:35:12,961 --> 00:35:14,661
And if you're looking
for a scalp,

904
00:35:14,696 --> 00:35:16,263
you can have mine.

905
00:35:16,298 --> 00:35:19,232
But I was under the impression
that this hearing

906
00:35:19,268 --> 00:35:21,301
was not about my old firm,
but whether or not

907
00:35:21,336 --> 00:35:24,805
Mr. Ross should be a lawyer.

908
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:26,406
I say he should.

909
00:35:26,442 --> 00:35:27,908
It doesn't matter
what you say.

910
00:35:27,943 --> 00:35:29,843
He's already had someone
testify for him.

911
00:35:29,878 --> 00:35:31,611
I'm not here to talk
about him.

912
00:35:31,647 --> 00:35:33,447
I'm here to talk
about someone else.

913
00:35:33,482 --> 00:35:34,692
Someone else
has nothing to do with this--

914
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:36,149
I'd like to hear this.

915
00:35:36,185 --> 00:35:38,952
15 years ago,
a young woman was arrested

916
00:35:38,987 --> 00:35:42,355
for illegally obtaining
prescription drugs.

917
00:35:42,391 --> 00:35:44,524
Turns out she had chronic pain

918
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:46,293
and didn't want
to drop out of med school,

919
00:35:46,328 --> 00:35:48,061
possibly never to return.

920
00:35:48,097 --> 00:35:51,131
So she stole
a couple of prescription pads

921
00:35:51,166 --> 00:35:53,133
from the hospital
where she was interning--

922
00:35:53,168 --> 00:35:56,536
a crime with a mandatory
sentence of seven years.

923
00:35:56,572 --> 00:36:00,107
But instead of throwing the book
at her,

924
00:36:00,142 --> 00:36:02,576
the prosecuting attorney
showed mercy,

925
00:36:02,611 --> 00:36:05,645
had the charges knocked down
to a misdemeanor,

926
00:36:05,681 --> 00:36:08,748
recommended probation,
and sealed the records.

927
00:36:08,784 --> 00:36:11,284
That's a touching story,
but I don't see

928
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,498
what a random attorney has to do
with these proceedings.

929
00:36:13,522 --> 00:36:15,489
She's not talking
about a random attorney.

930
00:36:15,524 --> 00:36:17,924
She's talking about me.

931
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:20,727
But just because
I showed compassion once

932
00:36:20,762 --> 00:36:22,729
doesn't mean he deserves it now.

933
00:36:22,764 --> 00:36:24,331
Maybe he doesn't.

934
00:36:24,366 --> 00:36:26,500
But that young woman
is now an ER doctor.

935
00:36:26,535 --> 00:36:28,435
She saves lives.

936
00:36:28,470 --> 00:36:32,939
And the world's a better place
because you saved hers.

937
00:36:32,975 --> 00:36:36,309
Thank you, Ms. Pearson.
Mr. Ross?

938
00:36:36,345 --> 00:36:41,948
<i>♪ ♪</i>

939
00:36:41,984 --> 00:36:45,752
I don't think
I can add anything to that.

940
00:36:45,787 --> 00:36:48,121
I've made my case.

941
00:36:48,157 --> 00:36:49,890
I leave the choice to you.

942
00:36:51,593 --> 00:36:53,860
Then this hearing
has concluded.

943
00:36:53,896 --> 00:36:56,963
We will deliberate and let you
know our decision by day's end.

944
00:36:56,999 --> 00:36:58,732
Thank you.

945
00:36:58,767 --> 00:37:05,772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

946
00:37:10,012 --> 00:37:11,745
So what do we do now?

947
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:13,825
They said they would let us
know by the end of the day.

948
00:37:13,849 --> 00:37:15,348
So we wait.

949
00:37:15,384 --> 00:37:16,828
Well, it is the end
of the day, which means...

950
00:37:16,852 --> 00:37:18,818
It doesn't mean anything,
Louis.

951
00:37:18,854 --> 00:37:21,166
Whatever's going on in there,
Seidel's gonna fight like hell.

952
00:37:21,190 --> 00:37:24,157
It's not gonna
make a difference.

953
00:37:24,193 --> 00:37:26,059
She's never gonna
change her mind.

954
00:37:26,094 --> 00:37:28,962
- I think she will.
- What do you mean?

955
00:37:28,997 --> 00:37:31,798
I mean that story
wasn't any old story,

956
00:37:31,833 --> 00:37:33,433
and that woman
wasn't really a woman.

957
00:37:33,468 --> 00:37:35,669
It was a man
named Joseph O'Neal.

958
00:37:35,704 --> 00:37:38,905
And it was
Walter Samson's godson.

959
00:37:38,941 --> 00:37:41,241
- So she did call in a favor.
- Yeah, she did.

960
00:37:41,276 --> 00:37:43,677
Then we need to get her
kicked off that board.

961
00:37:43,712 --> 00:37:45,445
No, Harvey. We don't.

962
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:46,691
Because I didn't fly
all the way down here

963
00:37:46,715 --> 00:37:48,248
to strong-arm that woman.

964
00:37:48,283 --> 00:37:50,050
And I know the story
of the wind and the sun.

965
00:37:50,085 --> 00:37:51,296
What the hell
are you talking about?

966
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:53,086
She's talking
about Aesop's fable.

967
00:37:53,121 --> 00:37:54,699
Which basically says
that if you want to get a man

968
00:37:54,723 --> 00:37:57,257
to take off his coat,
you don't blow it off.

969
00:37:57,292 --> 00:38:00,026
You make him feel warm, and
he'll take it off on his own.

970
00:38:00,062 --> 00:38:01,861
That's not a strategy;
it's a prayer.

971
00:38:01,897 --> 00:38:04,431
Louis, I already admitted
that I knew about Mike,

972
00:38:04,466 --> 00:38:07,234
and I reminded her
of her own compassion.

973
00:38:07,269 --> 00:38:10,103
That's the best
we're going to do.

974
00:38:10,138 --> 00:38:11,216
You know they could
disbar you for that.

975
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:12,806
In New York, they might.

976
00:38:12,841 --> 00:38:15,542
In Chicago,
nobody's gonna care.

977
00:38:15,577 --> 00:38:16,943
Thank you, Jessica.

978
00:38:16,979 --> 00:38:18,712
Don't thank me.
Thank Harvey.

979
00:38:18,747 --> 00:38:21,615
[phone vibrates]
He's the one that called me.

980
00:38:21,650 --> 00:38:23,183
It's Seidel.

981
00:38:24,586 --> 00:38:26,152
Hello.

982
00:38:29,925 --> 00:38:32,058
I'll tell him.

983
00:38:32,094 --> 00:38:34,327
Thanks for calling.

984
00:38:34,363 --> 00:38:38,298
<i>♪ ♪</i>

985
00:38:38,333 --> 00:38:39,299
You're in.

986
00:38:39,334 --> 00:38:42,736
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

987
00:38:42,771 --> 00:38:46,339
- [gasps] Oh, my God.
- [laughing]

988
00:38:46,375 --> 00:38:48,375
It happened.

989
00:38:48,410 --> 00:38:52,746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

990
00:38:52,781 --> 00:38:55,348
I'm gonna go get us
some champagne.

991
00:38:55,384 --> 00:38:59,519
- Thank you so much.
- [laughs]

992
00:38:59,554 --> 00:39:01,888
Thank you for flying in.

993
00:39:01,923 --> 00:39:04,357
I wouldn't miss this
for the world.

994
00:39:04,393 --> 00:39:11,097
<i>♪ ♪</i>

995
00:39:15,971 --> 00:39:17,804
Hey.

996
00:39:17,839 --> 00:39:20,573
You said you had to go to
the bathroom a half hour ago,

997
00:39:20,609 --> 00:39:22,709
but you never came back
for your champagne.

998
00:39:22,744 --> 00:39:24,944
I know.

999
00:39:24,980 --> 00:39:27,213
Louis, what's wrong?

1000
00:39:27,249 --> 00:39:29,215
You never asked me
how it went with Tara,

1001
00:39:29,251 --> 00:39:30,917
telling her about Mike.

1002
00:39:30,952 --> 00:39:32,819
I'm so sorry.

1003
00:39:32,854 --> 00:39:35,322
I just got caught up
with the hearing.

1004
00:39:35,357 --> 00:39:37,757
The thing is, I...

1005
00:39:37,793 --> 00:39:39,159
I told her.

1006
00:39:39,194 --> 00:39:41,328
We got into a huge fight.

1007
00:39:41,363 --> 00:39:43,563
And she said
she needed to think about

1008
00:39:43,598 --> 00:39:45,332
whether or not
she could forgive me.

1009
00:39:45,367 --> 00:39:46,766
- And?
- She just called

1010
00:39:46,802 --> 00:39:48,602
when Harvey was
giving us the news about Mike.

1011
00:39:48,637 --> 00:39:52,072
Left a 15-second voicemail.
I'm afraid to listen to it.

1012
00:39:52,107 --> 00:39:53,440
Louis...

1013
00:39:53,475 --> 00:39:55,019
She's either gonna tell me
that she never wants

1014
00:39:55,043 --> 00:39:57,944
to see me again
or she wants to make up.

1015
00:39:57,979 --> 00:40:00,180
Do you want me to listen
for you?

1016
00:40:00,215 --> 00:40:03,950
No. But I'd like it if
you stay with me while I do.

1017
00:40:03,985 --> 00:40:05,618
Of course.

1018
00:40:16,998 --> 00:40:19,966
<i>[poignant music]</i>

1019
00:40:20,001 --> 00:40:27,006
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1020
00:40:39,421 --> 00:40:42,422
[sobbing]

1021
00:41:06,148 --> 00:41:07,247
What's that?

1022
00:41:07,282 --> 00:41:09,115
I wanted to give you
a present.

1023
00:41:09,151 --> 00:41:11,317
Your first year's salary
in advance.

1024
00:41:11,353 --> 00:41:13,253
Welcome back.
Harvey, I'm running out

1025
00:41:13,288 --> 00:41:14,832
of ways to tell you I don't want
to be a corporate lawyer.

1026
00:41:14,856 --> 00:41:16,256
Before you answer,

1027
00:41:16,291 --> 00:41:18,091
you might want to take
a look at this check.

1028
00:41:18,126 --> 00:41:19,871
- You're trying to bribe me.
- I'm trying to close you.

1029
00:41:19,895 --> 00:41:21,694
- I told you--
- Yeah, I get it.

1030
00:41:21,730 --> 00:41:22,862
You want to do good.

1031
00:41:22,898 --> 00:41:24,464
Well,
you really want to do good?

1032
00:41:24,499 --> 00:41:26,099
Donate half of this
to the clinic.

1033
00:41:26,134 --> 00:41:27,667
You'll fund the place
for a year.

1034
00:41:27,702 --> 00:41:28,880
Oh, so that's what you think
I'm all about.

1035
00:41:28,904 --> 00:41:30,637
Just giving money.
No.

1036
00:41:30,672 --> 00:41:32,717
But I think you're about more
than just working at that place.

1037
00:41:32,741 --> 00:41:34,774
And you know it.
What are you talking about?

1038
00:41:34,810 --> 00:41:38,344
I'm offering you a deal.
One for you, one for me.

1039
00:41:38,380 --> 00:41:41,781
You can save the spotted owls,
stop global warming,

1040
00:41:41,817 --> 00:41:44,517
and help as many damsels
in distress as you like.

1041
00:41:44,553 --> 00:41:47,220
And the good news is,
you'll be doing it from here.

1042
00:41:47,255 --> 00:41:48,933
What makes you think
I'd take you up on that?

1043
00:41:48,957 --> 00:41:50,290
Because here's the thing,
Mike.

1044
00:41:50,325 --> 00:41:52,392
You wanna be here,
and you know it.

1045
00:41:52,427 --> 00:41:53,927
- That's not true--
- Uh-uh.

1046
00:41:53,962 --> 00:41:56,396
I saw the look on your face
when you strong-armed Palmer

1047
00:41:56,431 --> 00:41:59,732
and you took on Seidel and
every other talented attorney

1048
00:41:59,768 --> 00:42:01,935
you've beaten over the years.

1049
00:42:01,970 --> 00:42:02,936
And I told you this once before.

1050
00:42:02,971 --> 00:42:04,337
This is the major leagues.

1051
00:42:04,372 --> 00:42:05,972
You don't get
this feeling anywhere else.

1052
00:42:06,007 --> 00:42:08,675
And I'm offering you
the best of both.

1053
00:42:08,710 --> 00:42:11,678
<i>[light instrumentals]</i>

1054
00:42:11,713 --> 00:42:18,585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1055
00:42:18,620 --> 00:42:20,453
Why are you giving me
a peace sign?

1056
00:42:20,489 --> 00:42:22,188
- Double it.
- What?

1057
00:42:22,224 --> 00:42:23,634
I don't wanna just fund
the clinic for a year.

1058
00:42:23,658 --> 00:42:25,291
I wanna fund it for two.

1059
00:42:25,327 --> 00:42:27,293
And while we're at it,
I want some left over

1060
00:42:27,329 --> 00:42:29,440
for a little something nice
for me and the wife-to-be.

1061
00:42:29,464 --> 00:42:31,698
- That's all it's gonna take?
- Oh, not even close.

1062
00:42:31,733 --> 00:42:33,466
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

1063
00:42:33,502 --> 00:42:34,979
Any case I want to bring
the clinic on to, I can.

1064
00:42:35,003 --> 00:42:36,369
Done.

1065
00:42:36,404 --> 00:42:38,382
Anyone I want to bring over
from the clinic, I can.

1066
00:42:38,406 --> 00:42:40,974
Louis doesn't get a say,
you don't get a say,

1067
00:42:41,009 --> 00:42:43,843
no Harvard rule.
Done.

1068
00:42:43,879 --> 00:42:46,946
And there's one more thing,
and you're not gonna like it.

1069
00:42:46,982 --> 00:42:49,048
You are not getting
my office.

1070
00:42:49,084 --> 00:42:50,783
Oh, yes, I am.
And I will tell you why.

1071
00:42:50,819 --> 00:42:53,987
- Why?
- 'Cause she's gone, Harvey.

1072
00:42:54,022 --> 00:42:58,157
And she's not coming back.

1073
00:42:58,193 --> 00:43:00,760
It's time for you
to take the reins.

1074
00:43:00,795 --> 00:43:03,763
<i>[bluesy rock music]</i>

1075
00:43:03,798 --> 00:43:10,803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1076
